<p>Welfare Mobile: 07902292931</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h1>University Wide Services:&nbsp;</h1><h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>NIGHTLINE</strong></span><img style="float: right;" src="http://community.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/welfare/img/upload/002.jpg" alt="" width="152" height="163" /></h2><p><span style="color: black;">Nightline is a completely anonymous and confidential listening and information service which runs every night during term time between the hours of 9pm and 7am. The organisation is completely run by student volunteers, with two available each night for any Durham student to contact. We are non-judgemental and&nbsp;</span><span style="color: black; font-size: small;">have no religious or political affiliations</span><span style="color: black;">, so you can contact us about absolutely anything.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="color: black; font-size: small;">All aspects of your contact with Nightline will remain completely private and we will not push you to make any decisions or take a particular course of action. You can also call us for information, whether university related or for a taxi number, and we offer sexual health supplies such as condoms and chlamydia tests.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="color: black; font-size: small;">To call us, find the number on the back of your campus card or on DUO.</span><span style="color: black; font-size: small;"><br />Instant message us via the link on our website, <a href="http://community.dur.ac.uk/nightline">community.dur.ac.uk/nightline</a>.</span></p><div><p align="justify"><span style="color: black; font-size: small;">Drop-in and see us face-to-face in our office behind the Dun Cow Pub on Old Elvet</span></p><p align="justify">&nbsp;</p><h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Counselling service</span></h2><p>The counselling service is part of the university support network. Students can access the service to discuss issues that have been affecting their day to day lives and that may have had an impact on their work. The service is completely confidential. Drop-ins run Monday - Friday at 9am in the Palatine Centre where the service is based.&nbsp;</p></div><div>Phone: 0191 334 2200&nbsp;<br /> Email: <a href="mailto:counsel.service@durham.ac.uk">counsel.service@durham.ac.uk</a></div><div>Find out more&nbsp;<a href="https://www.dur.ac.uk/counselling.service/">https://www.dur.ac.uk/counselling.service/</a></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><a href="https://www.dur.ac.uk/counselling.service/"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="http://community.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/welfare/img/upload/003.jpg" alt="" /></a></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Disability Support</span></h2>The support for students with disabilities service aims to support students across the university who have any of the following which has an impact on your university experience:&nbsp;</div><div><ul><li>a recognised disability</li><li>specific learning difficulty</li><li>medical condition&nbsp;</li><li>mental health problem.&nbsp;</li></ul><br />Appointments, that are usually 45 minutes, are available Monday to Frida. The office is open 9am-5pm. In term time late night appointments are available 5pm-7pm. Monday to Thursday a drop-in service is offered between 10am and 4pm where you can access the office to see the Duty Advisor.&nbsp;</div><div><p>Mobile: 0789 504 2483</p><p>Email:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:disability.support@durham.ac.uk">disability.support@durham.ac.uk</a></p><p>Find out more&nbsp;<a href="https://www.dur.ac.uk/dussd/">https://www.dur.ac.uk/dussd/</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;">union advice and help service</span></h2>The service provides free advice and information to Durham University Students. It is situated in the&nbsp;Union building, Dunelm House. The team that work at the centre are professional and experienced advisors that can help on any topic of student life including money, housing and academic issues. The service is independent from the University and all enquiries will be dealt with in confidence. The service is open all year round.&nbsp;</div><div>You can make an appointment or contact the service for advice.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Phone: 0191 3341777</div><div>Email: <a href="mailto:dsu.advice@durham.ac.uk&nbsp;">dsu.advice@durham.ac.uk&nbsp;</a></div><div>Find out more&nbsp;<a href="http://www.durhamsu.com/main-menu/advice-and-help">http://www.durhamsu.com/main-menu/advice-and-help</a></div><div><a href="http://www.durhamsu.com/main-menu/advice-and-help"><img style="float: left;" src="http://community.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/welfare/img/upload/004.jpg" alt="" /></a></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div>